Author-Name: Esther Duflo  
Author-Name: Rema Hanna  
Author-Name: Stephen P. Ryan  
Title: Incentives Work: Getting Teachers to Come to School 
Abstract:
 We use a randomized experiment and a structural model to test whether
 monitoring and financial incentives can reduce teacher absence and
 increase learning in India. In treatment schools, teachers' attendance was
 monitored daily using cameras, and their salaries were made a nonlinear
 function of attendance. Teacher absenteeism in the treatment group fell by
 21 percentage points relative to the control group, and the children's
 test scores increased by 0.17 standard deviations. We estimate a
 structural dynamic labor supply model and find that teachers respond
 strongly to financial incentives. Our model is used to compute
 cost-minimizing compensation policies. (JEL I21, J31, J45, O15)
