Author-Name: Tobias Kretschmer  
Author-Name: Eugenio J. Miravete  
Author-Name: Jose C. Pernias  
Title: Competitive Pressure and the Adoption of Complementary Innovations 
Abstract:
 Liberalization of the European automobile distribution system in  2002
 limits the ability of manufacturers to impose vertical restraints, leading
 to a substantial increase in competitive pressure among  dealers. We
 estimate an equilibrium model of profit maximization to evaluate how
 dealers change their innovation adoption strategies  following the
 elimination of exclusive territories. Using French data we evaluate the
 existence of complementarities between the adoption  of software
 applications and the scale of production. Firms view these innovations as
 substitutes and concentrate their effort in one type of software as they
 expand their scale of production. Results are robust to the existence of
 unobserved heterogeneity. (JEL D24, K21, L21, L22, L62, O32)
