Author-Name: Simon Gilchrist  
Author-Name: Egon Zakrajsek  
Title: Credit Spreads and Business Cycle Fluctuations 
Abstract:
 Using micro-level data, we construct a credit spread index with
 considerable predictive power for future economic activity. We decompose
 the credit spread into a component that captures firm-specific information
 on expected defaults and a residual component--the excess bond premium.
 Shocks to the excess bond premium that are orthogonal to the  current
 state of the economy lead to declines in economic activity and asset
 prices. An increase in the excess bond premium appears to reflect a
 reduction in the risk-bearing capacity of the financial sector, which
 induces a contraction in the supply of credit and a deterioration in
 macroeconomic conditions.
